    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You are given a string of space-separated emoticons whose moods differ by expression. The happiness for each expression, in descending order, is shown below.<br><br>+1 <const>:)</const><br> 0  <const>:|</const><br>-1  <const>:(</const><br><br>However, not all people lean to the left. For example, <const>(:</const> is also happy, as is <const>):</const> sad.<br><br>Find the mean average happiness of all of the emoticons, round it to the nearest integer, and output an emoticon expressing this with its eyes to the left.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1: </strong><var>n</var><br><strong>Line 2: </strong><var>n</var> space-separated emoticons</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1: </strong>The leftward emoticon representing the average mood</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">2 &le; <var>n</var> &le; 16</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">3\n:) :| :(</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">:|</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
